## Restocking
Your shop stock of these bought-in goods is running low. You choose how much to buy.
- You have 1 ale on hand and room for 19 more at the most. It is generally worth about 1 coin each — pay much above that and you're overpaying.
  - Anders Brewer is here with you and sells ale. Buy it now — first call pay_with_item with seller "Anders Brewer", item "ale", a qty up to 19, and a payment: coins (amount), goods you carry (pay_items), or both, with consume_now false. Then also use speak for a brief handoff line as you make the offer. They will accept or counter your offer.

Weigh what's in front of you — obligations and pressing needs come before idle matters. Choose one action. After you speak, call done() and let others respond; speak again only if something new happens or someone asks you for more — never repeat or rephrase what you've already said.
